{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:24:43,076", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:24:43.076645\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Create a question generator that produces technical and behavioral interview questions based on the parsed job and resume data.\", \"result\": \"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"technical_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with Python. Can you provide an example of a challenging project where you used Python and the specific libraries or frameworks you utilized?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle performance optimization in that project?\\\",\\n        \\\"What testing strategies did you employ?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you manage dependencies?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Programming Languages\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"q...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"Here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The questions are generic and not parameterized by the parsed job/resume data. To generate tailored questions, use placeholders (e.g., {{primary_language}}, {{key_project}}) that a calling process can replace with actual values from the job description or candidate resume.\\n2. Add explicit metadata indicating which resume/job fields map to each placeholder so the generator knows what to pull.\\n3. Rename keys to emphasize these are “templates” rather than fixed questions.\\n\\nHere are the changes:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"technical_question_templates\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Programming Languages\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"primary_language\\\", \\\"key_project\\\", \\\"libraries_or_frameworks\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with {{primary_language}}. Can you provide an example of a challenging project (e.g., {{key_project}}) where you used {{primary_language}} and the specific libraries or frameworks ({{libraries_or_frameworks}}) you utilized?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle performance optimization in that {{key_project}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"What testing strategies did you employ for {{primary_language}} code?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you manage dependencies for {{libraries_or_frameworks}}?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Data Structures & Algorithms\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"algorithm_use_case\\\", \\\"chosen_data_structure\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Explain your understanding of data structures and algorithms. Can you describe a situation (e.g., {{algorithm_use_case}}) where you selected {{chosen_data_structure}} to optimize performance? What factors influenced your decision?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"What was the time complexity of your solution in the {{algorithm_use_case}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you validate the performance improvements?\\\",\\n        \\\"Were there any trade-offs in choosing {{chosen_data_structure}}?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Object-Oriented Programming\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"oop_project\\\", \\\"design_pattern\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Discuss your experience with object-oriented programming principles. How have you applied these principles in your {{oop_project}} to improve code maintainability and scalability?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"Can you give an example of using inheritance or polymorphism in {{oop_project}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"How do you ensure your classes remain loosely coupled?\\\",\\n        \\\"What design patterns (e.g., {{design_pattern}}) are you familiar with?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Databases\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"database_system\\\", \\\"complex_query\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with database management using {{database_system}}. Can you walk me through a complex SQL query ({{complex_query}}) you've written and explain how you optimized it for performance?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"What indexing strategies did you use in {{database_system}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you handle large datasets in {{database_system}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"Have you worked with other database systems besides {{database_system}}?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Cloud Platforms\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"cloud_service\\\", \\\"cloud_project\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Explain your experience with {{cloud_service}}. Can you describe a project ({{cloud_project}}) where you utilized {{cloud_service}} services? What were the benefits of using {{cloud_service}} in that context?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle security in your {{cloud_service}} environment?\\\",\\n        \\\"What cost-optimization strategies did you use?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you automate deployment and scaling on {{cloud_service}}?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Machine Learning\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"ml_project\\\", \\\"algorithm_type\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with machine learning. What types of algorithms (e.g., {{algorithm_type}}) have you worked with on {{ml_project}}, and how did you evaluate their performance?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle data preprocessing for {{ml_project}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"What metrics did you use to evaluate your {{algorithm_type}} model?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you address overfitting in {{ml_project}}?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"behavioral_question_templates\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Teamwork\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"team_project\\\", \\\"role\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work in a team on {{team_project}}. What was your role ({{role}}), and how did you contribute to the team's success?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle disagreements within the team?\\\",\\n        \\\"What did you learn from your role as {{role}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you ensure effective communication during {{team_project}}?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Problem Solving\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"tight_deadline_project\\\", \\\"obstacle\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time when you faced a tight deadline or unexpected obstacle ({{obstacle}}) while working on {{tight_deadline_project}}. How did you handle it and what was the outcome?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you prioritize tasks under pressure?\\\",\\n        \\\"Did you ask for help? From whom?\\\",\\n        \\\"What would you do differently next time?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Communication\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"tech_concept\\\", \\\"audience_type\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Describe a time when you had to explain {{tech_concept}} to a {{audience_type}}. How did you ensure they understood?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"What strategies did you use to simplify {{tech_concept}}?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you gauge their understanding?\\\",\\n        \\\"What was the result of your communication?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Initiative\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"initiative_project\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Give an example of a time you took initiative on {{initiative_project}}. What motivated you, and what was the result?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you identify the need for taking initiative?\\\",\\n        \\\"What obstacles did you face?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did your initiative benefit the project or team?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Feedback\\\",\\n      \\\"placeholder_keys\\\": [\\\"feedback_scenario\\\"],\\n      \\\"question_template\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time you received negative feedback about {{feedback_scenario}}. How did you respond?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_templates\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you process the feedback?\\\",\\n        \\\"What steps did you take to improve?\\\",\\n        \\\"What did you learn from that experience?\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 17:24:59,667", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_3\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation for a candidate.\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct  interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Ask follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task0:\\n  Objective: Implement a module to parse and analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes, producing structured feature data and match indicators.\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"job_description_analysis\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n    \\\"required_skills\\\": [\\n      \\\"Python\\\",\\n      \\\"Data Structures\\\",\\n      \\\"Algorithms\\\",\\n      \\\"Object-Oriented Programming\\\",\\n      \\\"Database Management\\\",\\n      \\\"Communication\\\",\\n      \\\"Teamwork\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"preferred_skills\\\": [\\n      \\\"Machine Learning\\\",\\n      \\\"Cloud Computing (AWS, Azure, GCP)\\\",\\n      \\\"Agile Methodologies\\\",\\n      \\\"DevOps\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"experience_level\\\": \\\"Mid-Level\\\",\\n    \\\"education_requirements\\\": \\\"Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field\\\",\\n    \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n      \\\"Design, develop, and maintain software applications\\\",\\n      \\\"Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code\\\",\\n      \\\"Collaborate with cross-functional teams\\\",\\n      \\\"Participate in code reviews\\\",\\n      \\\"Troubleshoot and debug issues\\\",\\n      \\\"Contribute to system architecture and design\\\"\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"resume_analysis\\\": {\\n    \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n    \\\"skills\\\": [\\n      \\\"Python\\\",\\n      \\\"Data Structures\\\",\\n      \\\"Algorithms\\\",\\n      \\\"Object-Oriented Programming\\\",\\n      \\\"SQL\\\",\\n      \\\"Machine Learning\\\",\\n      \\\"AWS\\\"\\n    ],\\n    \\\"experience\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"company\\\": \\\"ABC Company\\\",\\n        \\\"dates\\\": \\\"2018-2022\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n          \\\"Developed and maintained Python-based applications\\\",\\n          \\\"Designed and implemented database schemas\\\",\\n          \\\"Deployed applications on AWS\\\",\\n          \\\"Collaborated with team members on projects\\\"\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"title\\\": \\\"Intern\\\",\\n        \\\"company\\\": \\\"XYZ Company\\\",\\n        \\\"dates\\\": \\\"2017\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n          \\\"Assisted in the development of web applications\\\",\\n          \\\"Wrote unit tests\\\",\\n          \\\"Participated in code reviews\\\"\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"education\\\": {\\n      \\\"degree\\\": \\\"Bachelor of Science in Computer Science\\\",\\n      \\\"university\\\": \\\"University of California, Berkeley\\\",\\n      \\\"graduation_date\\\": \\\"2018\\\"\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \\\"match_indicators\\\": {\\n    \\\"required_skills_total\\\": 7,\\n    \\\"required_skills_matched\\\": 5,\\n    \\\"required_skill_match_ratio\\\": 0.71,\\n    \\\"preferred_skills_total\\\": 4,\\n    \\\"preferred_skills_matched\\\": 2,\\n    \\\"preferred_skill_match_ratio\\\": 0.50,\\n    \\\"experience_level_match\\\": true,\\n    \\\"education_match\\\": true,\\n    \\\"overall_match_score\\\": 0.78,\\n    \\\"responsibility_keywords_matched\\\": 7\\n  },\\n  \\\"extracted_features\\\": {\\n    \\\"programming_languages\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"SQL\\\"],\\n    \\\"data_structures\\\": [\\\"Data Structures\\\"],\\n    \\\"algorithms\\\": [\\\"Algorithms\\\"],\\n    \\\"object_oriented_programming\\\": [\\\"Object-Oriented Programming\\\"],\\n    \\\"databases\\\": [\\\"SQL\\\"],\\n    \\\"cloud_platforms\\\": [\\\"AWS\\\"],\\n    \\\"machine_learning\\\": [\\\"Machine Learning\\\"],\\n    \\\"methodologies\\\": [\\\"Agile (inferred)\\\", \\\"DevOps (inferred)\\\"],\\n    \\\"soft_skills\\\": [\\\"Communication\\\", \\\"Teamwork\\\"],\\n    \\\"tools_and_frameworks\\\": []\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nTask task1:\\n  Objective: Create a question generator that produces technical and behavioral interview questions based on the parsed job and resume data.\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"technical_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with Python. Can you provide an example of a challenging project where you used Python and the specific libraries or frameworks you utilized?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle performance optimization in that project?\\\",\\n        \\\"What testing strategies did you employ?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you manage dependencies?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Programming Languages\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain your understanding of Data Structures and Algorithms. Can you describe a situation where you had to choose a specific data structure or algorithm to optimize performance? What factors influenced your decision?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"What was the time complexity of your solution?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you validate the performance improvements?\\\",\\n        \\\"Are there any trade-offs to your chosen approach?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Data Structures & Algorithms\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Discuss your experience with Object-Oriented Programming principles. How have you applied these principles in your previous projects to improve code maintainability and scalability?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"Can you give an example of using inheritance or polymorphism?\\\",\\n        \\\"How do you ensure your classes are loosely coupled?\\\",\\n        \\\"What design patterns are you familiar with?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Object-Oriented Programming\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with database management, specifically using SQL. Can you walk me through a complex SQL query you've written and explain how you optimized it for performance?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"What indexing strategies did you use?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you handle large datasets?\\\",\\n        \\\"What database systems have you worked with?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Databases\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain your experience with AWS. Can you describe a project where you utilized AWS services? Which services did you use, and what were the benefits of using AWS in that context?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle security in your AWS environment?\\\",\\n        \\\"What strategies did you use for cost optimization?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you automate deployment and scaling?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Cloud Platforms\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with Machine Learning. What types of machine learning algorithms have you worked with, and how did you evaluate their performance? Please provide a specific example.\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle data preprocessing?\\\",\\n        \\\"What metrics did you use to evaluate your model?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you address overfitting?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Machine Learning\\\"\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"behavioral_questions\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work in a team to solve a complex problem. What was your role, and how did you contribute to the team's success?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you handle disagreements within the team?\\\",\\n        \\\"What did you learn from the experience?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you ensure effective communication?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Teamwork\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time when you had to deal with a tight deadline or unexpected obstacle while working on a project. How did you handle the situation, and what was the outcome?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you prioritize tasks?\\\",\\n        \\\"Did you ask for help? If so, from whom?\\\",\\n        \\\"What would you do differently next time?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Problem Solving\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe a time when you had to explain a technical concept to a non-technical audience. How did you ensure they understood the information?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"What strategies did you use to simplify the explanation?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did you gauge their understanding?\\\",\\n        \\\"What was the result of the communication?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Communication\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"question\\\": \\\"Give an example of a time you took initiative on a project. What motivated you to do so, and what was the result?\\\",\\n      \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n        \\\"How did you identify the need for initiative?\\\",\\n        \\\"What obstacles did you face?\\\",\\n        \\\"How did your initiative benefit the project or team?\\\"\\n      ],\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"Initiative\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n       \\\"question\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time you received negative feedback. How did you respond?\\\",\\n       \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n         \\\"How did you process it?\\\",\\n         \\\"What steps did you take?\\\",\\n         \\\"What did you learn?\\\"\\n       ],\\n       \\\"category\\\": \\\"Feedback\\\"\\n     }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Develop an answer evaluation component that assesses each candidate response for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy, outputting evaluation metrics.\\nTask task6:\\n  Objective: Assemble the final candidate evaluation report in plain text, combining resume-job match analysis, interview summary, technical and behavioral assessments, strengths/weaknesses, recommendation, and scoring breakdown.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nBuild an interview engine to conduct the interview session, present generated questions, capture candidate responses, and dynamically trigger follow-up questions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nJSON\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interview_session\\\": {\\n    \\\"candidate_name\\\": \\\"John Doe\\\",\\n    \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n    \\\"date\\\": \\\"2024-01-01\\\",\\n    \\\"interviewer\\\": \\\"Recruiter Name\\\",\\n    \\\"sections\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"section_name\\\": \\\"Technical Assessment\\\",\\n        \\\"questions\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"T1\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with Python. Can you provide an example of a challenging project where you used Python and the specific libraries or frameworks you utilized?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate described a project involving data analysis where they used Pandas and Scikit-learn. They discussed the challenges of handling large datasets and optimizing performance.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T1.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you handle performance optimization in that project?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate explained their use of vectorization and efficient data structures to improve processing speed.\\\"\\n              },\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T1.2\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"What testing strategies did you employ?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate discussed using unit tests and integration tests to ensure code quality.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"T2\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Explain your understanding of Data Structures and Algorithms. Can you describe a situation where you had to choose a specific data structure or algorithm to optimize performance? What factors influenced your decision?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate described a scenario where they used a hash map to optimize search operations in a large dataset. They explained the trade-offs between time and space complexity.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T2.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"What was the time complexity of your solution?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate stated the time complexity was O(1) on average for search operations.\\\"\\n              },\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T2.2\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you validate the performance improvements?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate mentioned using benchmarking tools to measure the execution time before and after the optimization.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"T3\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Discuss your experience with Object-Oriented Programming principles. How have you applied these principles in your previous projects to improve code maintainability and scalability?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate explained their understanding of encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism, and provided examples of how they used these principles to create modular and reusable code.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T3.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"Can you give an example of using inheritance or polymorphism?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate gave example of using inheritance to implement different types of data processors.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"T4\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with database management, specifically using SQL. Can you walk me through a complex SQL query you've written and explain how you optimized it for performance?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate detailed experience in query optimization, using indexes, and writing stored procedures. They gave an example of a complex query used to generate reports.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T4.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"What indexing strategies did you use?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate mentioned using clustered and non-clustered indexes based on the query patterns.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"T5\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Explain your experience with AWS. Can you describe a project where you utilized AWS services? Which services did you use, and what were the benefits of using AWS in that context?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate described a project where they used EC2 for compute, S3 for storage, and Lambda for serverless functions. They mentioned the benefits of scalability and cost-effectiveness.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T5.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you handle security in your AWS environment?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate described using IAM roles and security groups to control access to AWS resources.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n                   {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"T6\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Describe your experience with Machine Learning. What types of machine learning algorithms have you worked with, and how did you evaluate their performance? Please provide a specific example.\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate detailed experience with linear regression, logistic regression, and support vector machines. They described a project with model building and evaluation.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"T6.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you handle data preprocessing?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate mentioned techniques of normalization and feature scaling.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"section_name\\\": \\\"Behavioral Assessment\\\",\\n        \\\"questions\\\": [\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"B1\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Describe a situation where you had to work in a team to solve a complex problem. What was your role, and how did you contribute to the team's success?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate described a project where they worked with a cross-functional team to develop a new feature for a web application. They highlighted their role in designing and implementing the user interface.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"B1.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you handle disagreements within the team?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate stated they encourage all members to voice concerns.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"B2\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time when you had to deal with a tight deadline or unexpected obstacle while working on a project. How did you handle the situation, and what was the outcome?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate recounted a situation where a critical database server failed just before a major product launch. They described their efforts to quickly diagnose the problem and implement a workaround.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"B2.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you prioritize tasks?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate prioritized the critical tasks.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"B3\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Describe a time when you had to explain a technical concept to a non-technical audience. How did you ensure they understood the information?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate described a time when they had to explain the benefits of a new software system to a group of business stakeholders. They focused on using clear and concise language and avoiding technical jargon.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"B3.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"What strategies did you use to simplify the explanation?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate mentioned using analogies and real-world examples to illustrate the concepts.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"B4\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Give an example of a time you took initiative on a project. What motivated you to do so, and what was the result?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate recalled implementing a new code review process.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"B4.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you identify the need for initiative?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate noticed increasing bug reports.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          },\\n          {\\n            \\\"question_id\\\": \\\"B5\\\",\\n            \\\"question_text\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time you received negative feedback. How did you respond?\\\",\\n            \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate shared receiving feedback about documentation.\\\",\\n            \\\"follow_up_questions\\\": [\\n              {\\n                \\\"follow_up_id\\\": \\\"B5.1\\\",\\n                \\\"follow_up_text\\\": \\\"How did you process it?\\\",\\n                \\\"candidate_response\\\": \\\"The candidate reevaluated their strategy.\\\"\\n              }\\n            ]\\n          }\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:24:59.667032\"\n}"}
